				<h2>Motor Controller Power Supply</h2>
<p>I have an Orange Pi which I would like to use as the computer for a robotic project. It supplies around 15&nbsp;mAh power directly from the board, barely enough for a single LED so I will have to use a motor controller and an external power supply. </p>

<p>My question is, is there a limit to how big of a motor I use with this small orange Pi zero? As long as I have the appropriate power supply and controller for the motor I feel it shouldn't be an issue.</p>

<p>What are some things to keep in mind?</p>

